headline: Coca-Cola invests some $90 million to expand production in Brazil's Amazonas
summary: Coca-Cola Brasil invested 550 million reais ($91 million) to expand a concentrate beverage plant in the Brazilian state of Amazonas, the company said in a statement. The new plant was inaugurated on Friday in the presence of Brazil's Vice President Geraldo Alckmin and other official authorities, Coca-Cola said. ($1 = 6.0379 reais)
